Feature Engineering : Feature Engineering is the process of creating, modifying, or selecting features (columns) in a dataset to improve the performance of a machine learning model.
                      Simply, it means making the data more useful for prediction.
Feature Engineering is important for : 1. Improves model accuracy.
                                       2. Makes patterns easier to learn.
                                       3. Reduces unnecessary information.
                                       4. Helps models perform better.
Common Feature Engineering Techniques :
1. Creating New Features : Create a new column from existing columns.
2. Encoding Categorical Data : Convert text into numbers.
3. Feature Scaling : Bring numerical values to a similar range.
4. Feature Selection : Select only the important columns.
PCA(Principal Component Analysis) : PCA is a dimensionality reduction technique that converts many related features into a smaller number of new features called Principal Components,
                                    while keeping most of the important information.
PCA is used for : 1. Reduce dimensions
                  2. Remove redundant features
                  3. Speed up training
                  4. Improve visualization
                  5. Reduce noise
Handling Imbalanced Data : Imbalanced data means one class has many more records than another class.
Techniques : 
1. Oversampling : Increase minority class samples.
2. Undersampling : Reduce majority class samples.
3. SMOTE (Synthetic Minority Oversampling Technique) : Creates new synthetic (artificial) minority samples instead of simply copying existing ones.
4. ADASYN (Adaptive Synthetic Sampling) : An improved version of SMOTE.
                                          Creates more synthetic samples for difficult-to-learn minority instances.
5. Tomek Links : Removes overlapping samples between classes to make the class boundary clearer.
Pattern Detection : Pattern Detection means finding useful trends or relationships in the data.
Anomaly Identification : Anomaly Identification means detecting unusual or abnormal data points that are very different from the rest.
                         These unusual points are called anomalies or outliers.
